{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e1210d87-5be3-496e-b3db-99967dba8bf2","content":"Good news — with .NET 10 SDK, `dotnet test` **natively** speaks the Microsoft.Testing.Platform protocol. You **no longer need `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`**. That property was the bridge for .NET 9 and earlier SDKs; in .NET 10 it's a no-op.\n\nJust remove it:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_8FRacPr4SJqqjPAm2Fq0E2","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Removing obsolete MTP property"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"tooluse_liFE3dVKuh1jAGdOEsTX1T","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-3d7eb7d581cc4b5d833b7b7997dc7727/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>","new_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-3d7eb7d581cc4b5d833b7b7997dc7727/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"47fcd870-1a4a-4a87-b201-6f7b76951819","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK (10.0.100) and using MSTest with Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) via `EnableMSTestRunner` and `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`.\n\nWith .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively supports Microsoft.Testing.Platform without needing the `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property. In .NET 10, MTP integration is built into `dotnet test` directly.\n\nKey changes for .NET 10:\n1. `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` is no longer needed — .NET 10's `dotnet test` natively uses MTP when it detects a test project is MTP-enabled (which it is when `EnableMSTestRunner` is set to true).\n\n\n2. I'll remove that property from their project file and show them the updated configuration.","outputTokens":527},"id":"5a9fcf8b-c9ec-487b-ad30-20bb5e595b08","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:47:23.553Z","parentId":"9c536e0f-bdba-4e38-a48d-488e95dbdb55"}
